When I was walking through the aisles of that store, what struck me most wa=
s the fact that grocers aren=E2=80=99t just doing a job or running a compan=
y. In many cases, they=E2=80=99re supporting families, neighborhoods, and e=
ntire communities =E2=80=94 just like they have for generations. That exper=
